Register präzise erschlossen. Neben den Kompositionen Martin Colers werden in einem Anhang die früheren, 1648 publizierten 19 Lieder aus der Feder Hinrich Papes sowie die trotz des Verlustes des Drucks von 1661 teilweise sekundär überlieferten geistlichen Lieder Colers aus den Rist gewidmeten ‚Opfern, die GOtt gefallen‘ von Brandanus Langejanus mitgeteilt.Die Edition ist geeignet, unerwartete Einblicke in die Theologie-, Literatur- und Musikgeschichte der Barockzeit zu gewähren.   aPresented for the first time in a historical-critical edition, Passion Devotions is Rist’s twelfth collection of hymns and the last of his sacred works to be published during his lifetime. It is the product of Rist’s fruitful cooperation with the Wolfenbüttel Choirmaster Martin Coler, and an extraordinary lyrical example of the multiple facets of Baroque Lutheran passion theology and piety.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 4a17. Jahrhundert. 4aBarockliteratur. 4aBaroque (music). 4aDeutsche Literatur. 4aKirchenlieder. 4aPassionsmusik. 4aRist, Johann. 4apassion (music). 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh1 aColer, Martin, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHernández Castelló, Esteban1 aHuck, Oliver1 aSteiger, Johann Anselm, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literature 2014z9783110370331oZDB-23-DLW0 cEPUBz97831103872610 cprintz978311037379040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311037647040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110376470423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/978311037647